    "description": "Berlanga de Duero is a Spanish municipality located in the province of Soria, in the autonomous region of Castile and León. An object dubbed the \"Berlanga cup\" was discovered here. This object is a hemispherical bowl that belongs to a small group of artifacts referred to as \"Hadrian's Wall pans\", as these vessels depict places and names from sites along the line of Hadrian's Wall.",
